<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Find a Contractor</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="preparation">Even the handiest of homeowners need assistance with renovations occasionally .</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1002" relname="joint">From new construction to tear downs ,</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="1004" relname="span">help from an expert may be needed</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="4" relname="purpose">to ensure the job gets completed correctly .</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1007" relname="span">Before calling the first name</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">you come across in your phone book or on the Internet ,</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1008" relname="span">consider the following advice</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="8" relname="circumstance">when trying to find a contractor .</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1011" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="1011" relname="joint">Seek advice from family and friends .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1014" relname="attribution">Ask people</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="1014" relname="span">you know and trust for a recommendation</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="13" relname="condition">if they have had similar work done in their homes .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1016" relname="span">You will feel more confident</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1017" relname="span">in calling a contractor</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="16" relname="elaboration">who has made your best friend or brother happy with the renovation .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1019" relname="span">Consult with professionals</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="18" relname="elaboration">you already know .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1023" relname="condition">If you have a great electrician or plumber ,</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="1023" relname="joint">he has experience with reliable contractors</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1023" relname="joint">and will not hesitate to provide you with names and numbers .</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="1024" relname="span">Your professional will not recommend someone</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="23" relname="elaboration">he would n't use .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1011" relname="joint">Collect more than one contractor estimate .</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1027" relname="span">Make sure that you have at least 3 contractors bid on your home renovation project</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1028" relname="span">rather than hiring the first one</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="27" relname="elaboration">that walks through your front door .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1031" relname="span">When you sit down</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="29" relname="purpose">to compare ,</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1033" relname="span">the work</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="31" relname="elaboration">that was quoted by each contractor</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="1032" relname="same_unit">should be similar in its specifications .</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1035" relname="preparation">Examine business cards .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1036" relname="same_unit">A contractor should provide a business card</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="37" relname="circumstance">when meeting you ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1037" relname="span">and that card needs to have a physical address , telephone number and a license number .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1039" relname="preparation">Once she leaves ,</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="1039" relname="joint">verify the information and the status of her license .</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1039" relname="joint">Check references .</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1039" relname="joint">A decent contractor will not hesitate to provide a written list of references ,</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1043" relname="same_unit">and the longer the list ,</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="1044" relname="span">the more likely</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="43" relname="elaboration">he is reputable .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1046" relname="span">Call as many on the list</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="1047" relname="span">until you have the information</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="46" relname="elaboration">you need .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1051" relname="span">A tip</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="purpose">to ensure quality</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1050" relname="same_unit">is to skip around the list</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="1052" relname="span">instead of going in the order</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="51" relname="elaboration">provided .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1039" relname="joint">Verify insurance information .</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="55" relname="condition">When you are meeting with a prospective contractor ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1055" relname="span">ask her to show you an insurance certificate .</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1056" relname="span">In the alternative , you can request the contractor 's insurance carrier and telephone number</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="58" relname="attribution">so that you can be sure</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1057" relname="span">the policy is in good standing .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="1059" relname="preparation">Warnings</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="preparation">Beware of cash .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1062" relname="span">When you find a contractor</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="61" relname="elaboration">that you like ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1061" relname="span">ask how he expects to be paid .</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1065" relname="span">The one</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="64" relname="elaboration">who wants all cash</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="span">may be cutting corners</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">that will also cut the quality of the job</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="67" relname="elaboration">done in your home .</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1069" relname="preparation">Drop a contractor without a cell phone .</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1070" relname="span">Almost every professional has a cell phone ,</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1071" relname="same_unit">so</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="73" relname="condition">if you find a contractor without one ,</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1072" relname="span">do not hire her .</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1074" relname="span">A contractor should provide you with means</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="74" relname="purpose">to reach her easily .</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1076" relname="span">Question the contractor</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="76" relname="elaboration">who eliminates the permit .</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="79" relname="condition">If your renovation project is substantial ,</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1078" relname="span">you will most likely need a construction permit .</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1080" relname="condition">If the contractor suggests skipping this paperwork ,</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1081" relname="attribution">it could mean</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1081" relname="contrast">that he is n't licensed</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1081" relname="contrast">or does n't want to be monitored .</segment>
